solutions.content:
Check whether num + k and num - k are already in the set and also make sure the pair is not already counted. Only goes throught the list one time.

Edit: after reading other solutions, some memory can be saved by only saving the smallest value between num1 and num2 in pairsSet instead of the sorted tuple.
```
class Solution(object):
    def findPairs(self, nums, k):
        if k < 0: return 0
        numsSet, pairsSet = set(), set()
        for num1 in nums:
            for num2 in [num1 + k, num1 - k]:
                if num2 in numsSet:
                    pairsSet.add(tuple(sorted([num1, num2])))
            numsSet.add(num1)
        return len(pairsSet)
```

