solutions.content:
**Explaination :**

1. Use some kind of sorting mechanism. To sort the array. Also don't include duplicates in this array.
2. Also store the frequency of each element in another Array.
3. Use two pointers (ptr1 and ptr2). And move these two according to the difference between the elements.
    while(untill ptr2 reaches the end of sorted array)
        - If difference == k  : increment ptr1 and ptr2 and sum++
        - if difference < k : increment ptr2
        - if difference >k : increment ptr1
        - Special case - if k==0 and difference == k and freq >1 :  increment ptr1 and ptr2 and sum++ 

**Approach :**

**Contraints hint:**
Firstly, to get better understanding of how to proceed, I looked up to the contraints. And as the length of array will be always less than 10^4 . This means, we cannot use O(n^2) . We can use sorting because that would give O(nlogn) complexity, which is fair enough.

**Examples hint:**
Now if we try some examples. we can think whether we need duplicate? How are duplicated causing any problem? And if we see, for the much part, it is of no use. We can ignore duplicates. Because questions asks to find **unique pairs** only. So if we have two 1s and single 3, like this : arr= [1,1,3] and k = 2;
then (arr[0] , arr[2] ) and (arr[1] , arr[2]) are counted only once. And ans = 1.

Similarly , if arr= [1,1,3,3] and k =2;
Still ans = 1;

So, We dont need duplicates here. We can count them once. 

**Edge cases hint:**
On, further trying out example, **if k= 0,**  then what are the challenges:
if k == 0 then the difference has to be 0. But , according to the question, in a k-diff pair : (arr[i] , arr[j]) , **i != j**
So , it must be same integer but at different index in sorted array. Then we can consider it in our mighty Answer!
Ex : arr= [1,1,2,3,4] and k = 0
ans = 1 (arr[0] , arr[1])

So here we need to keep in mind the **role of duplicates, when k==0.**
And , knowing that a value freq is stricly more than 1, and k==0 , we can count it in the answer.

*My mighty code:*

```
class Solution {
public:
    int findPairs(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        map<int,int> mp;    //creating map with frequency as its value
        for(int i = 0; i<nums.size(); i++){
            mp[nums[i]]+=1;
        }
        int sum = 0;
       map<int,int>::iterator itl;   //ptr1
        map<int,int>::iterator itr;   //ptr2
        itl= mp.begin(); itr= mp.begin() ;

        while(itr!=mp.end()){
            int f = itl->first;
            int s = itr -> first;
            if(s-f <k && s>=f){
                itr++;   //increment ptr2 -> increase window width
            }else if(s-f > k && s>=f){
                itl++;   //increment ptr1 -> decrease window width
            }else if(s-f == k){
                if((k==0 && itl->second >1 )|| (k>0)){
                    sum++;
                }
                itr++; itl++;  //increment both ptr1 and ptr2 -> sliding the window
            }

        }

        return sum;
    }
};
```

