solutions.content:
Nice beginner string parsing problem.

In order to solve it, we will declare a few support variable:
* `res` is our accumlator variable for the final result;
* `r1`, `i1`, `r2`, `i2`, `res1` and `res2` are our container for the extracted and computed real and imaginary parts.

We will start with a simple extraction, calling `getReal` on `n1` and `n2`.

This helper function will get a string `s`and declare a few support variables, all initialised to `0`/`false`:
* `r` and `i` will store the real and imaginary part, respectively;
* `j` will be our pointer while parsing the input string;
* `isNeg` is a boolean to keep track of the initial sign.

We will then:
* iterate while `s[j] != '+'` (which is guaranted to be there and:
	* if `s[j]` is `'-'`, we will flag `isNeg` to be `true`;
	* otherwise we will increase `r` to be `10` times its previous value plus `s[j] - '0'`;
	* increase `j` by `1`;
* if `isNeg` was flagged, we will flip `r`'s sign and reset `isNeg` to be `false`;
* increase `j` by `1`, to skip `'+'`;
* iterate while `s[j] != '+'` (which is guaranted to be there and:
	* if `s[j]` is `'-'`, we will flag `isNeg` to be `true`;
	* otherwise we will increase `i` to be `10` times its previous value plus `s[j] - '0'`;
	* increase `j` by `1`;
* if `isNeg` was flagged, we will flip `i`'s sign;
* `return` `r` and `i` as a pair.

Once we are done with the parsing part, we can store the real and imaginary part of the result into `res1` and `res2` respectively, turn them into strings and finally join them together with `'+'` and appending `'i'` to `res` before returning it. :)

The code:

```cpp
class Solution {
    pair<int, int> getReal(string s) {
        // support variables
        int r = 0, i = 0, j = 0;
        bool isNeg = false;
        // getting the real part
        while (s[j] != '+') {
            if (s[j] == '-') isNeg = true;
            else r = r * 10 + s[j] - '0';
            j++;
        }
        if (isNeg) r *= -1, isNeg = false;
        // getting the imaginary part
        j++;
        while (s[j] != 'i') {
            if (s[j] == '-') isNeg = true;
            else i = i * 10 + s[j] - '0';
            j++;
        }
        if (isNeg) i *= -1;
        return {r, i};
    }
public:
    string complexNumberMultiply(string n1, string n2) {
        // support variables
        string res;
        int r1, i1, r2, i2, res1, res2;
        // reading the input
        tie(r1, i1) = getReal(n1);
        tie(r2, i2) = getReal(n2);
        // res1 is now the real part of the result
        res1 = r1 * r2 - i1 * i2;
        // res2 is now the imaginary part of the result
        res2 = r1 * i2 + i1 * r2;
        // composing res
        res = to_string(res1);
        res.push_back('+');
        res += to_string(res2);
        res.push_back('i');
        return res;
    }
};
```

