# Intuition
Given two strings representing complex numbers, our task is to multiply them and return the result as a string. A complex number can be represented as a + bi, where a and b are real numbers and i is the imaginary unit. The product of two complex numbers (a + bi) * (c + di) can be calculated using the formula (ac - bd) + (ad + bc)i.
# Approach
Parse the input strings to extract the real and imaginary parts of the complex numbers.
Calculate the real and imaginary parts of the product using the formula (ac - bd) + (ad + bc)i.
Construct the result string in the format a + bi.
To parse the input strings, we can use the stringstream class to read data from the strings into integer and character variables. We can then perform the multiplication and construct the result string using another stringstream.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string complexNumberMultiply(string a, string b) {
        int a1, a2, b1, b2;
        char op;
        stringstream sa(a), sb(b), ans;
        sa >> a1 >> op >> a2 >> op;
        sb >> b1 >> op >> b2 >> op;
        ans << a1 * b1 - a2 * b2 << "+" << a1 * b2 + a2 * b1 << "i";
        return ans.str();
    }
};
```

